      ],
      "explanation": "The mean is sensitive to extreme values (outliers), while the median is resistant. In right-skewed data: mean > median. In left-skewed: mean < median. The answer is 'When data is skewed or has outliers'. The other options — 'When all values are equal', 'When data has no mode', and 'When the sample size is small' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
